<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 25 at 5:06PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light rain has developed this evening leading to potentially
slick conditions...
Light rain has developed over areas where road surface conditions
are at or below freezing, where any surfaces that look wet could
be icy and may result in locally slick conditions through the
overnight hours. Black ice is a driving hazard and is defined as
patchy ice on roadway surfaces that cannot easily be seen. It is
often clear with the road surface visible underneath. Use caution
if traveling on area roads this afternoon as black ice is
difficult for drivers to see and avoid.</description>
